about.summary: Functions for Maximum Likelihood (ML) estimation and non-linear optimization, and related tools.  It includes a unified way to call different optimizers, and classes and methods to handle the results from the ML viewpoint.  It also includes a number of convenience tools for testing and developing your own models.

name: r-maxlik
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.3-8" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-maxlik
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/maxLik_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/maxLik/maxLik_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 33404d10bfe7746cab8227b880b50808a63909036daf6fedbac94c75ac68dfe5

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-misctools >=0.6_8
    - r-sandwich
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-misctools >=0.6_8
    - r-sandwich

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('maxLik')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('maxLik')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=maxLik
  license: GPL (>= 2)
  summary: Functions for Maximum Likelihood (ML) estimation and non-linear optimization, and
    related tools.  It includes a unified way to call different optimizers, and classes
    and methods to handle the results from the ML viewpoint.  It also includes a number
    of convenience tools for testing and developing your own models.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
